body:
RT, for example: 
```
module SameIdentifier;

typedef struct packed {
    logic [3:0] id;
    logic [7:0] addr;
} Contact;

Contact Contact;

initial begin
    Contact = { 4'h2, 8'h9 };
    $display("id: %0d, addr: %0d", Contact.id, Contact.addr);
end 

endmodule
```
verilator --sc --debug --gdbbt same_identifier.v

When verilated, it will get an error: 
```
%Error: same_identifier.v:8:9: syntax error, unexpected TYPE-IDENTIFIER
    8 | Contact Contact;
      |         ^~~~~~~
%Error: same_identifier.v:11:15: syntax error, unexpected '{', expecting new or new-then-paren
   11 |     Contact = { 4'h2, 8'h9 };
      |               ^
```
